          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_VCzzxV": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Question two: does your skin react?</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_rqLQr7": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The second question is whether your skin is <strong>reactive</strong>, and it's the one people most often get wrong, because almost everyone feels their skin is a little sensitive. So set the feeling aside and look for the signs instead.</p><p><strong>Reactive skin</strong> tends to sting or prickle when you try something new, before it settles, if it settles at all. It reddens or goes blotchy easily, in cold wind, after a hot shower, or for no obvious reason. It can feel tight, itchy or rough, and it reacts in situations where most skin wouldn't. If several of those ring true and they happen often rather than once in a blue moon, your skin is probably on the sensitive side. If new products generally sit fine and your skin stays fairly even, it probably isn't.</p><p>Reactivity mostly shows up at the two ends of the spectrum, with dry or oily skin, rather than in the calm middle. Balanced skin that reacts strongly is genuinely uncommon.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
